                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480612-name-255" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-255" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-255" type="surname" value="FRIEND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-255" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FRIEND</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Eastbourne-terrace, Hyde-park. The prisoner was in my service about twelve months, and left about three weeks ago, without notice; he merely went out on a message—I missed a pair of boots—these are them (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—they were kept in the scullery.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480612-name-256" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-256" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-256" type="surname" value="DOWSETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-256" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY DOWSETT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, D</hi> 181.) I took the prisoner on 19th May, and told him it was for stealing a pair of boots of his master's—he said his mistress lent them to him, and they were on his feet—he had on these boots produced.</p>
               <p>----<hi rend="smallCaps">FRIEND</hi>. I am the prosecutor's wife—I did not give or lend the prisoner the boots.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. You asked me to go and pawn some plate for you; I said, "I have got these boots to pawn;" you said if I made haste back with the money I might go out for an hour or two; I did so, and you said I might go; I went to the theatre, got back late, and was afraid to come home.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. It is entirely false.</p>
